Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

donor_enumerator.py:
- Add SOFT_METAL_SUBTYPES, HARD_METAL_SUBTYPES, BORDERLINE_SUBTYPES pools
  stratified by Pearson HSAB softness.
- Add _get_subtypes_for_metal(): HSAB-guided pool selection (soft>0.60
  gets Se/Te/P/As/C-cyanide; hard<0.25 gets O/F/N-hard; auto otherwise).
- Wire HSAB pool into enumerate_donor_sets() — replaces flat CORE_SUBTYPES.
- Expand MAX_DONOR_COUNT: Se, Te, As, Sb, F, C, N_oxime, S_sulfoxide, etc.
- Expand CHELATE_PAIRS: Se/N, Se/Se, P/S, P/Se, P/N, As/As, As/P, oxime.
- Expand COMPATIBLE_GROUPS: selenolate, selenoether, P/Se, P/S, cyanide, F.
- Add 17 new ARCHETYPES:
    selenocysteine-type (SeN), bis/tetra selenolate, bis(SeN2),
    selenacrown-12/18, mixed [12]aneS2Se2, bis/tetra bisphosphine,
    phosphino-thiolate, phosphino-selenolate, bis/tetra arsine,
    hexacyanometallate, tetracyanometallate, DMG-type bis-oxime,
    tetrafluoride, fluorocarboxylate chelate, [12]aneS4, [18]aneS6.

design_engine.py:
- Add design_mode parameter: 'auto'|'soft'|'hard'|'cross_modal'.
    auto        — HSAB-guided (default, inferred in enumerator).
    soft        — Force SOFT_METAL_SUBTYPES (Se/Te/P/As/C donors).
    hard        — Force HARD_METAL_SUBTYPES (O/F/hard-N donors).
    cross_modal — Macrocyclic archetypes only (filters non-macrocyclic).
- Expand METAL_ALIASES: Ru, Os, Rh, Ir, Mo, W, Re, Ge, Zr, Hf, Ti4+, Be.
- Expand MATRIX_PRESETS: precious_metals_leach, gold_cyanide, e_waste,
  nuclear_waste, chloralkali_brine, pgm_leach, rare_earth.

Tests: 44 new in test_design_engine_expansion.py; 561 total pass, 0 fail.
